-- Kapchorua Tea of Kenya First-Half Profit More Than Doubles as Sales Jump
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-29T06:32:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-29/kapchorua-tea-of-kenya-first-half-profit-more-than-doubles-as-sales-jump.html
Kapchorua Tea Co., a Kenyan producer
of the leaves, said first-half profit doubled as sales
increased.  Net income surged to 92.2 million shillings ($1.14 million)
in the six months through September from 44.8 million shillings
a year earlier, the company said in a statement distributed by
the Nairobi Stock Exchange today. Sales climbed 41 percent to
604 million shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  